title: Simple performance improvement @ Rootbeer.isRooted
message:
Simple performance improvement @ Rootbeer.isRooted

Even though it facilitates debugging, the way the code was written would cause all the root checks to be executed, even when the first check already detected that the device was rooted.

The way the code is written now, the method can return as soon as one of the methods (in order) detects that the device is rooted, and the other methods in the OR chain don't need to be executed.
